		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: PAL Mattel NES overclock?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Within the standard caveats about overclocking the NES (at some point things will crash <a href="http://www.racketboy.com/retro/experimenting-with-nes-overclocking" class="postlink">(synopsis of results from a defunct webpage)</a> ; different games will have different maximum speeds; the PPU still has to be clocked at the normal speed ; the music will get noticeably higher), and the standard caveats about the range of fundamental frequency crystals (you can't get crystals faster than about 33MHz, above that you'll have to use an oscillator-in-a-can)... sure, it'll work.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


