		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Nalchlan wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I've not seen the two legged crystals used, as I believed they were for radios?<br /></div>The two-legged crystals need an external driver, such as a BJT or a specific IC. A lot of microcontrollers have the driver integrated.<br />The four-pin devices include that driver so that it just produces the desired signal on output.

		

